&gt; are attached to corresponding signatures in a parent class.
&gt; (only class level annotation inheritance)
&gt;
&gt; I wanted something like:
&gt; public abstract class ApiTestBase
&gt; {
&gt;   @BeforeClass abstract void suiteSetup() throws Exception;
&gt;   @Before abstract void preTest() throws Exception;
&gt;   @Test abstract void Run() throws Exception;
&gt;   @After abstract void postTest() throws Exception;
&gt;   @AfterClass abstract void suiteTearDown() throws Exception;
&gt; }
&gt; so that the subclass would just have to implement the
&gt; required methods without having to explicitly re-annotate.
